{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BExVy2Q8CBmrgNQDDZxVu5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package protocol\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bytes\"\n     5→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"io\"\n     8→\t\"time\"\n     9→)\n    10→\n    11→type MessageType string\n    12→\n    13→const (\n    14→\tMsgStepStarted  MessageType = \"step_started\"\n    15→\tMsgStepCompleted MessageType = \"step_completed\"\n    16→\tMsgRunCompleted  MessageType = \"run_completed\"\n    17→\tMsgRunTitle      MessageType = \"run_title\"\n    18→\tMsgLog           MessageType = \"log\"\n    19→\tMsgError         MessageType = \"error\"\n    20→)\n    21→\n    22→type StatusMessage struct {\n    23→\tType      MessageType `json:\"type\"`\n    24→\tStepName  string      `json:\"step_name,omitempty\"`\n    25→\tResult    string      `json:\"result,omitempty\"`\n    26→\tMessage   string      `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n    27→\tTimestamp time.Time   `json:\"timestamp\"`\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→// flusher is an optional interface for writers that support explicit flushing.\n    31→type flusher interface {\n    32→\tFlush() error\n    33→}\n    34→\n    35→type StatusWriter struct {\n    36→\tw   io.Writer\n    37→\tenc *json.Encoder\n    38→}\n    39→\n    40→func NewStatusWriter(w io.Writer) *StatusWriter {\n    41→\treturn &StatusWriter{w: w, enc: json.NewEncoder(w)}\n    42→}\n    43→\n    44→func (s *StatusWriter) StepStarted(stepName string) {\n    45→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgStepStarted, StepName: stepName})\n    46→}\n    47→\n    48→func (s *StatusWriter) StepCompleted(stepName, result string) {\n    49→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgStepCompleted, StepName: stepName, Result: result})\n    50→}\n    51→\n    52→func (s *StatusWriter) RunCompleted(result string) {\n    53→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgRunCompleted, Result: result})\n    54→}\n    55→\n    56→func (s *StatusWriter) RunTitle(title string) {\n    57→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgRunTitle, Message: title})\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→func (s *StatusWriter) Log(stepName, message string) {\n    61→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgLog, StepName: stepName, Message: message})\n    62→}\n    63→\n    64→func (s *StatusWriter) Error(stepName, message string) {\n    65→\ts.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgError, StepName: stepName, Message: message})\n    66→}\n    67→\n    68→func (s *StatusWriter) write(msg StatusMessage) {\n    69→\tmsg.Timestamp = time.Now()\n    70→\t_ = s.enc.Encode(msg)\n    71→\t// Flush the underlying writer if it supports it, to ensure real-time delivery.\n    72→\tif f, ok := s.w.(flusher); ok {\n    73→\t\t_ = f.Flush()\n    74→\t}\n    75→}\n    76→\n    77→func ParseStatusStream(data []byte) ([]StatusMessage, error) {\n    78→\tvar msgs []StatusMessage\n    79→\tdec := json.NewDecoder(bytes.NewReader(data))\n    80→\tfor dec.More() {\n    81→\t\tvar msg StatusMessage\n    82→\t\tif err := dec.Decode(&msg); err != nil {\n    83→\t\t\treturn msgs, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to decode status message: %w\", err)\n    84→\t\t}\n    85→\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, msg)\n    86→\t}\n    87→\treturn msgs, nil\n    88→}\n    89→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LUR8zLT62d8pbFKzq3zGR4","session_id":"a767d320-7441-4cfb-80d2-26edf647ec06","uuid":"33988f69-386a-43d5-89eb-65ddae0d7c60"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"aca5029d31df2f418","tool_use_id":"toolu_01LUR8zLT62d8pbFKzq3zGR4","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore codebase structure","usage":{"total_tokens":75826,"tool_uses":45,"duration_ms":123506},"uuid":"4b5a65ac-b7dc-42d9-87d6-64c8dedbbb59","session_id":"a767d320-7441-4cfb-80d2-26edf647ec06"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LUR8zLT62d8pbFKzq3zGR4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed report:\n\n## Cloche Codebase Architecture & Implementation Guide\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's the complete breakdown of how the system works:\n\n---\n\n### 1. BINARIES & ENTRY POINTS\n\n#### **cmd/cloche/ - CLI Client** (Short-lived)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Commands** (29 total):\n  - No-daemon commands: `init`, `health`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `project`, `validate`\n  - Daemon commands (need gRPC): `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n  - Special: `help`, `--version`\n\n- **Key Commands Structure**:\n  - `cmdRun()`: Takes `--workflow`, `--prompt (-p)`, `--title`, `--issue (-i)`, `--keep-container`. Resolves image from workflow file and calls `RunWorkflow()` gRPC RPC\n  - `cmdStatus()`: Shows daemon/project overview or individual run details\n  - `cmdLogs()`: Streams logs via `StreamLogs()` gRPC RPC\n  - `cmdStatusProject()`: Shows project-specific info (active loops, runs, success rate)\n\n#### **cmd/cloched/ - Daemon** (Long-running)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  1. Opens gRPC server on `unix:///` socket or TCP\n  2. Initializes `ContainerRuntime` (Docker or local)\n  3. Sets up SQLite store, log broadcaster, evolution trigger\n  4. Auto-runs active projects' host workflows on startup\n  5. Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n  6. Optional: HTTP web dashboard on `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n\n- **Auto-Run Logic** (`autoRunActiveProjects()`):\n  - Scans all projects, finds those with `config.Active == true`\n  - Checks for `.cloche/host.cloche` existence\n  - Launches `host.Runner.Run()` in background goroutine per project\n\n#### **cmd/cloche-agent/ - In-Container Agent** (Autonomous)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n- **Takes**: Workflow file path as CLI arg (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`)\n- **Execution**:\n  1. Parses workflow DSL via `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n  2. Creates `stepExecutor` with adapters (generic, prompt)\n  3. Runs workflow via `engine.Run()`\n  4. Streams JSON-line status messages to stdout (parsed by daemon)\n  5. Returns exit code (0 = success, non-zero = failure)\n\n---\n\n### 2. gRPC SERVICE DEFINITION\n\n**File**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n#### **Core RPCs**:\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest)` → `RunWorkflowResponse`\n  - Input: `workflow_name`, `project_dir`, `image`, `prompt`, `keep_container`, `title`, `issue_id`\n  - Returns: `run_id` (immediately; container runs in background)\n  \n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest)` → `GetStatusResponse`\n  - Returns: current state, active steps, step executions, container info\n  \n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest)` → `stream LogEntry`\n  - Supports: `run_id`, `step_name`, `log_type`, `follow` (tail -f mode), `limit`\n  \n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest)` → `ListRunsResponse`\n  - Filters: `project_dir`, `state`, `task_id`, `limit`\n  \n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest)`, `DeleteContainer()`, `Shutdown()`, `GetVersion()`\n\n#### **Loop Management**:\n- `EnableLoop(project_dir, max_concurrent)` - Activate auto-run\n- `DisableLoop()` - Deactivate \n- `ResumeLoop()` - Resume after halt\n- `GetProjectInfo()` - Detailed project state including loop status, active runs, evolution toggle\n\n---\n\n### 3. DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n\n#### **Run** (`run.go`)\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID              string           // Unique run ID (e.g., \"develop-lush-fern\")\n    WorkflowName    string\n    State           RunState         // pending|running|succeeded|failed|cancelled\n    ActiveSteps     []string         // Currently executing step names\n    StepExecutions  []*StepExecution // History of all step runs\n    StartedAt       time.Time\n    CompletedAt     time.Time\n    ProjectDir      string\n    ErrorMessage    string\n    ContainerID     string           // Docker container ID (if container run)\n    BaseSHA         string           // Git HEAD at run start (for branch extraction)\n    ContainerKept   bool             // true if --keep-container was used\n    Title           string           // One-line summary\n    IsHost          bool             // true for host workflow runs\n    ParentRunID     string           // ID of parent (host) run if child\n    TaskID          string           // Associated task ID (from loop)\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string            // Step name\n    Result      string            // success|fail|<custom>\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string            // Output state/branch\n}\n```\n\n#### **Workflow** (`workflow.go`)\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire            // (from_step, result) → [to_steps]\n    Collects  []Collect         // Fan-in: wait for multiple (step, result) pairs\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string // e.g., \"container.image\", \"host.agent_command\"\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string            // Step identifier\n    Type    StepType          // agent|script|workflow\n    Results []string          // Declared result names (e.g., [\"success\", \"fail\"])\n    Config  map[string]string // e.g., \"run\", \"prompt\", \"workflow_name\", \"max_attempts\"\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string           // Step name\n    Result    string           // Result to trigger on\n    To        string           // Target step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping  // Extract vars from step output\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string      // Environment variable name\n    Path   OutputPath  // JSON path (e.g., .result[0].id)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. PORTS & INTERFACES\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n#### **AgentAdapter** - Executes a single agent step\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\nImplementations:\n- `prompt.Adapter` - Claude Code / agent commands\n- `generic.Adapter` - Shell script execution\n\n#### **ContainerRuntime** - Docker/local execution\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\n// Optional interface\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n#### **RunStore** - Persistence\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx, run *domain.Run) error\n    ListRuns(ctx) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. ADAPTERS\n\n#### **Docker Runtime** (`internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`)\n**Start Process**:\n1. Build `docker create` command with args:\n   - `--workdir /workspace`\n   - `--user root` (for default cmd wrapper)\n   - `-e CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run_id>`\n   - Copy ANTHROPIC_API_KEY if set\n   - Support `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` and `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n\n2. Copy project to container via `docker cp` (no bind mount)\n3. Copy `.cloche/overrides/` on top (optional)\n4. Copy Claude auth files (`~/.claude/`, `~/.claude.json`)\n5. Start container with `docker start`\n\n**Default Command Wrapper** (when using standard agent):\n- Root user runs chown + cleanup script\n- Strips `.serena` directory (performance)\n- Disables plugins in `.claude/settings.json`\n- Execs as `agent` user with actual command\n\n#### **Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n**Configuration**:\n- `Commands`: Ordered fallback chain (e.g., `[\"claude\"]`)\n- `ExplicitArgs`: Override default args (e.g., `[\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\"]`)\n- `StatusWriter`: Optional real-time output streaming\n\n**Execution Flow**:\n1. Check `max_attempts` config; return `\"give-up\"` if exceeded\n2. Increment attempt counter\n3. Assemble full prompt (see `assemblePrompt()`)\n4. Try each command in fallback chain:\n   - Parse stdin as prompt\n   - Capture stdout (or stream via StatusWriter)\n   - Extract Claude Code stream-json events:\n     - `\"assistant\"` events → extract text + tool summaries\n     - `\"result\"` events → final result with CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n5. Classify result:\n   - Exit 0 + output = `\"success\"` (or marker result)\n   - Exit 0 + no output = `\"fail\"` (auth/config error)\n   - Exit non-zero + marker = marker result\n   - Exit non-zero + no marker = `\"fail\"` + error message\n6. On success, reset attempt counter; write output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n**Stream JSON Parsing** (`extractStreamText()`):\n- Decodes JSON event, identifies type\n- `\"assistant\"`: Extracts text blocks + tool_use summaries (e.g., \"--- Tool: Read('file.txt') ---\")\n- `\"result\"`: Contains final text with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker\n\n#### **Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`)\n**Execution**:\n1. Run shell command via `sh -c`\n2. Pass env vars: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`\n3. Capture stdout (optional: stream via StatusWriter)\n4. Extract result marker from output\n5. Write cleaned output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n---\n\n### 6. EXECUTION ENGINE\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n**Workflow Execution Model**:\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor      // Delegates step execution\n    status         StatusHandler     // Status callbacks\n    maxSteps       int               // Limit (default 1000)\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration     // Per-step timeout\n}\n\n// Main loop algorithm:\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**Algorithm**:\n1. Validate workflow + config\n2. Create Run, mark as running\n3. Launch entry step in goroutine\n4. Event loop processes results channel:\n   - **On step complete**:\n     - Record result\n     - Lookup wires for `(step, result)` pair\n     - Launch target steps (fanout support)\n     - Fire matching `collect` conditions\n   - **On wire missing**: Check if any collect handles it; error if neither\n   - **On execution error**: Fail workflow\n5. Track `doneCount` and `aborted` flag\n6. Determine final state:\n   - `aborted` OR error → `RunStateFailed`\n   - `doneCount > 0` → `RunStateSucceeded`\n   - Else → `RunStateFailed`\n\n**Concurrency**:\n- Each step runs in separate goroutine\n- Results channel for completion signaling\n- Main loop is single-threaded (protects Run state)\n\n**Timeouts**:\n- Per-step timeout from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Fallback to engine default (30 min)\n- Context cancellation kills step goroutine\n\n---\n\n### 7. DAEMON gRPC SERVER\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n#### **ClocheServer Structure**:\n```go\ntype ClocheServer struct {\n    store        ports.RunStore\n    captures     ports.CaptureStore\n    logStore     ports.LogStore\n    container    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    defaultImage string\n    evolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    logBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    runIDs       map[string]string      // run_id → container_id\n    loops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir → orchestration loop\n}\n```\n\n#### **RunWorkflow() RPC Flow**:\n1. Check if workflow is host or container (`host.FindHostWorkflows()`)\n2. **If host**: Call `runHostWorkflow()` → dispatch to `host.Runner` → return immediately\n3. **If container**:\n   - Generate unique run ID\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run_id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Create Run record in store (state: pending)\n   - Launch `launchAndTrack()` in background\n   - Return run_id immediately\n\n#### **launchAndTrack() Background Process**:\n1. Ensure image exists (rebuild if Dockerfile changed)\n2. Capture git HEAD SHA (for result branch creation)\n3. Start container via `container.Start()`\n4. Update Run: state=running, containerID=X\n5. Call `trackRun()` to monitor agent output\n\n#### **trackRun() - Status Parsing**:\n1. Attach to agent stdout via `container.AttachOutput()`\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages:\n   ```go\n   type StatusMessage struct {\n       Type      MessageType  // step_started|step_completed|run_completed|run_title|log|error\n       StepName  string\n       Result    string\n       Message   string\n       Timestamp time.Time\n   }\n   ```\n3. Handle each message:\n   - `step_started`: Record in Run.ActiveSteps\n   - `step_completed`: Update Run.StepExecutions\n   - `run_title`: Set Run.Title if empty\n   - `run_completed`: Capture reported result\n   - `error`: Capture error message\n   - `log`: Publish via logBroadcast (for cloche logs)\n\n4. Extract output files from container to `.cloche/<run_id>/output/`\n5. Extract results to git branch (`cloche/<run_id>` branch) via `docker.ExtractResults()`\n6. Finalize Run state:\n   - If `reportedResult == \"succeeded\"` → `RunStateSucceeded`\n   - Else → `RunStateFailed`\n7. Fire evolution trigger if configured\n8. Container cleanup:\n   - Failed runs: always keep\n   - Successful + `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful, no `--keep-container`: remove\n\n---\n\n### 8. HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTION\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` + `executor.go`\n\n#### **Runner - Orchestration**:\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher       // Dispatches container workflows\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    Captures      ports.CaptureStore\n    LogBroadcast  *logstream.Broadcaster\n    TaskID        string              // From daemon loop\n    ExtraEnv      []string            // Additional env vars\n    SkipRunRecord bool                // For list-tasks polling\n}\n```\n\n**Execution** (`runNamedWorkflow()`):\n1. Find workflow in `.cloche/*.cloche` files\n2. Create output directory `.cloche/<run_id>/output`\n3. Create host Run record (if not skipping)\n4. Create Executor + Engine\n5. Run workflow via engine\n6. Persist final state\n7. Return RunResult\n\n#### **Executor - Step Implementation**:\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string              // Host project root\n    MainDir       string              // Worktree dir for scripts\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string              // `.cloche/<run_id>/output/`\n    Wires         []domain.Wire       // For output mappings\n    HostRunID     string              // Parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string            // Workflow-level agent config\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n```\n\n**Step Types**:\n\n1. **Script** (`executeScript()`):\n   - Run shell command via `sh -c`\n   - Working dir: MainDir (worktree) or ProjectDir\n   - Env vars:\n     - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=<project>`\n     - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=<run_id>/<step>.out`\n     - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run_id>`\n     - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID=<task_id>` (if set)\n     - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=<previous_step_output>` (if available)\n     - Resolved output mappings from wires\n   - Extract result marker from output\n   - Write output to `.cloche/<run_id>/output/<step>.out`\n\n2. **Workflow** (`executeWorkflow()`):\n   - Dispatch container workflow via gRPC RPC\n   - Read prompt from previous step output (or `prompt_step` override)\n   - Link child run to parent (set `ParentRunID`)\n   - Poll run state every 2 seconds until terminal\n   - Map run state to result: `succeeded` → `success`, else → `fail`\n   - Write run ID to step output (for downstream steps)\n\n3. **Agent** (`executeAgent()`):\n   - Use prompt adapter (Claude Code)\n   - Workflow/step-level agent config (commands, args)\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run_id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Execute adapter\n   - Copy output to executor's output dir\n\n**Output Mappings** (`resolveOutputMappings()`):\n- For each wire to step with output mappings:\n  - Read source step's output\n  - Evaluate path (JSON navigation)\n  - Return `KEY=value` strings\n  - Add to step's environment\n\n---\n\n### 9. HOST ORCHESTRATION LOOP\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n**Orchestration Loop** (`Loop` struct):\n- Monitors project for task changes (via `list-tasks` workflow)\n- Auto-runs main/evolve workflows based on:\n  - `config.Concurrency` (max parallel runs)\n  - `config.StaggerSeconds` (delay between launches)\n  - `config.DedupSeconds` (coalesce rapid task updates)\n  - `config.StopOnError` (halt on unrecovered error)\n  - Evolution-discovered improvements\n\n**Workflow Types**:\n1. `list-tasks`: Discovers available tasks\n2. `main`: Primary task execution (container workflow dispatch)\n3. `evolve`: Self-improvement (powered by evolution trigger)\n4. `finalize`: Post-run cleanup/merge (if defined)\n\n---\n\n### 10. CLI AGENT (PROMPT ADAPTER)\n\n**Key Feature - Conversation Resume via `-c` flag**:\n\nThe prompt adapter in host.cloche can resume Claude Code conversations:\n\n```go\n// From prompt.go:\ndefaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n}\n\n// Conversation IDs passed via env or config:\n// CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND=\"claude -c <conversation_id>\"\n```\n\n**Stream JSON Processing**:\n- Claude Code emits `--output-format stream-json`\n- Each line is a JSON event:\n  - `\"assistant\"` type: New message with content blocks\n  - `\"result\"` type: Final result with CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- Adapter extracts text and tool summaries in real-time\n- Publishes to logBroadcaster for `cloche logs` streaming\n\n---\n\n### 11. WORKFLOW DSL\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Syntax Example**:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n    container {\n        image: \"cloche-agent:latest\"\n        agent_command: \"claude\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"analyze\" {\n        agent\n        prompt: \"prompts/analyze.txt\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n        max_attempts: \"3\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"test\" {\n        script\n        run: \"make test\"\n        results: [\"pass\", \"fail\"]\n        timeout: \"10m\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"merge\" {\n        script\n        run: \"git merge main\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"conflict\"]\n    }\n    \n    analyze: success → test\n    test: pass → merge\n    test: fail → done\n    merge: success → done\n    merge: conflict → abort\n}\n```\n\n**Host Workflow Example**:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n    host {\n        agent_command: \"claude\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"generate\" {\n        agent\n        prompt: \"prompts/task.txt\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    step \"run_workflow\" {\n        workflow_name: \"develop\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    step \"merge\" {\n        script\n        run: \"bash scripts/merge.sh\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    generate: success → run_workflow\n    run_workflow: success → merge\n    merge: success → done\n    merge: fail → abort\n}\n```\n\n**Key Parsing Features**:\n- `ParseAll()`: Multiple workflows, auto-detects host vs container\n- `host {}` or `container {}` blocks determine location\n- Workflow-level + step-level config inheritance\n- Output mapping syntax: `output.map: { STEP_VAR: \".path.to.field\" }`\n- Collects: Fan-in multiple branches with `collect all|any`\n\n---\n\n### 12. KEY FILES REFERENCE\n\n| Component | File(s) |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **CLI** | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` |\n| **Daemon** | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` |\n| **Agent** | `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` |\n| **Domain** | `/workspace/internal/domain/{run,workflow}.go` |\n| **Ports** | `/workspace/internal/ports/{agent,container,store}.go` |\n| **gRPC** | `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` + `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` |\n| **Docker** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` |\n| **Prompt Adapter** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` |\n| **Generic Adapter** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` |\n| **Engine** | `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` |\n| **Host Runner** | `/workspace/internal/host/{runner,executor}.go` |\n| **DSL Parser** | `/workspace/internal/dsl/{parser,lexer}.go` |\n| **SQLite Store** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` |\n| **Status Protocol** | `/workspace/internal/protocol/{status,result}.go` |\n\n---\n\n### 13. EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─ CLI: cloche run --workflow develop\n│\n├─→ gRPC: RunWorkflow()\n│\n├─→ [Container Workflow]\n│   ├─ Create Run (pending)\n│   ├─ Start Docker container (async)\n│   ├─ Agent runs: engine.Run(workflow)\n│   │  ├─ Launch entry step (goroutine)\n│   │  ├─ Await result via channel\n│   │  ├─ Wire to next steps\n│   │  └─ Repeat until done/abort\n│   ├─ Parse agent status JSON → update Run\n│   ├─ Extract output files from container\n│   ├─ Extract results to git branch\n│   └─ Finalize Run state\n│\n└─ [Host Workflow]\n    ├─ Create Run (host=true)\n    ├─ host.Runner.Run(project, \"main\")\n    ├─ Parse host.cloche\n    ├─ Execute steps via Executor:\n    │  ├─ Script: sh -c <cmd>\n    │  ├─ Workflow: dispatch container via gRPC (wait)\n    │  └─ Agent: prompt adapter on host\n    ├─ Record step outputs in .cloche/<run_id>/output/\n    └─ Finalize host Run state\n```\n\n---\n\nThis architecture enables **self-evolving containerized development workflows** with strong separation of concerns: domain logic, storage, container runtimes, and agent adapters are all pluggable via ports."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aca5029d31df2f418 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 81949\ntool_uses: 45\nduration_ms: 123509</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a767d320-7441-4cfb-80d2-26edf647ec06","uuid":"cbf06bd1-b0cc-4d7f-b729-f2d6903449a4","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. How existing CLI commands are structured (look at cmd/cloche/ - especially how commands like `run`, `stop`, `logs`, `status` are implemented)\n2. The gRPC service definitions (proto files) - what RPCs exist\n3. The domain types - Run, Step, Result, Workflow\n4. The ports/interfaces - especially RunStore, AgentAdapter, ContainerRuntime\n5. How the daemon handles workflow execution (both host and container)\n6. How the agent executes steps (especially script vs prompt steps)\n7. How Claude Code agent adapter works (the -c flag for conversation resume)\n\nSearch very thoroughly across:\n- cmd/cloche/\n- cmd/cloched/\n- cmd/cloche-agent/\n- internal/domain/\n- internal/ports/\n- internal/adapters/\n- internal/host/\n- api/ or proto/ (gRPC definitions)\n\nFor each area, show me the key types, functions, and how they connect.","agentId":"aca5029d31df2f418","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me create a detailed report:\n\n## Cloche Codebase Architecture & Implementation Guide\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's the complete breakdown of how the system works:\n\n---\n\n### 1. BINARIES & ENTRY POINTS\n\n#### **cmd/cloche/ - CLI Client** (Short-lived)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Commands** (29 total):\n  - No-daemon commands: `init`, `health`, `get`, `set`, `tasks`, `workflow`, `project`, `validate`\n  - Daemon commands (need gRPC): `run`, `status`, `logs`, `poll`, `list`, `stop`, `delete`, `loop`, `shutdown`\n  - Special: `help`, `--version`\n\n- **Key Commands Structure**:\n  - `cmdRun()`: Takes `--workflow`, `--prompt (-p)`, `--title`, `--issue (-i)`, `--keep-container`. Resolves image from workflow file and calls `RunWorkflow()` gRPC RPC\n  - `cmdStatus()`: Shows daemon/project overview or individual run details\n  - `cmdLogs()`: Streams logs via `StreamLogs()` gRPC RPC\n  - `cmdStatusProject()`: Shows project-specific info (active loops, runs, success rate)\n\n#### **cmd/cloched/ - Daemon** (Long-running)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n- **Responsibilities**:\n  1. Opens gRPC server on `unix:///` socket or TCP\n  2. Initializes `ContainerRuntime` (Docker or local)\n  3. Sets up SQLite store, log broadcaster, evolution trigger\n  4. Auto-runs active projects' host workflows on startup\n  5. Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n  6. Optional: HTTP web dashboard on `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n\n- **Auto-Run Logic** (`autoRunActiveProjects()`):\n  - Scans all projects, finds those with `config.Active == true`\n  - Checks for `.cloche/host.cloche` existence\n  - Launches `host.Runner.Run()` in background goroutine per project\n\n#### **cmd/cloche-agent/ - In-Container Agent** (Autonomous)\n- **File**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n- **Takes**: Workflow file path as CLI arg (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`)\n- **Execution**:\n  1. Parses workflow DSL via `dsl.ParseForContainer()`\n  2. Creates `stepExecutor` with adapters (generic, prompt)\n  3. Runs workflow via `engine.Run()`\n  4. Streams JSON-line status messages to stdout (parsed by daemon)\n  5. Returns exit code (0 = success, non-zero = failure)\n\n---\n\n### 2. gRPC SERVICE DEFINITION\n\n**File**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n#### **Core RPCs**:\n- `RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest)` → `RunWorkflowResponse`\n  - Input: `workflow_name`, `project_dir`, `image`, `prompt`, `keep_container`, `title`, `issue_id`\n  - Returns: `run_id` (immediately; container runs in background)\n  \n- `GetStatus(GetStatusRequest)` → `GetStatusResponse`\n  - Returns: current state, active steps, step executions, container info\n  \n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest)` → `stream LogEntry`\n  - Supports: `run_id`, `step_name`, `log_type`, `follow` (tail -f mode), `limit`\n  \n- `ListRuns(ListRunsRequest)` → `ListRunsResponse`\n  - Filters: `project_dir`, `state`, `task_id`, `limit`\n  \n- `StopRun(StopRunRequest)`, `DeleteContainer()`, `Shutdown()`, `GetVersion()`\n\n#### **Loop Management**:\n- `EnableLoop(project_dir, max_concurrent)` - Activate auto-run\n- `DisableLoop()` - Deactivate \n- `ResumeLoop()` - Resume after halt\n- `GetProjectInfo()` - Detailed project state including loop status, active runs, evolution toggle\n\n---\n\n### 3. DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n\n#### **Run** (`run.go`)\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID              string           // Unique run ID (e.g., \"develop-lush-fern\")\n    WorkflowName    string\n    State           RunState         // pending|running|succeeded|failed|cancelled\n    ActiveSteps     []string         // Currently executing step names\n    StepExecutions  []*StepExecution // History of all step runs\n    StartedAt       time.Time\n    CompletedAt     time.Time\n    ProjectDir      string\n    ErrorMessage    string\n    ContainerID     string           // Docker container ID (if container run)\n    BaseSHA         string           // Git HEAD at run start (for branch extraction)\n    ContainerKept   bool             // true if --keep-container was used\n    Title           string           // One-line summary\n    IsHost          bool             // true for host workflow runs\n    ParentRunID     string           // ID of parent (host) run if child\n    TaskID          string           // Associated task ID (from loop)\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string            // Step name\n    Result      string            // success|fail|<custom>\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string            // Output state/branch\n}\n```\n\n#### **Workflow** (`workflow.go`)\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire            // (from_step, result) → [to_steps]\n    Collects  []Collect         // Fan-in: wait for multiple (step, result) pairs\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string // e.g., \"container.image\", \"host.agent_command\"\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string            // Step identifier\n    Type    StepType          // agent|script|workflow\n    Results []string          // Declared result names (e.g., [\"success\", \"fail\"])\n    Config  map[string]string // e.g., \"run\", \"prompt\", \"workflow_name\", \"max_attempts\"\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n    From      string           // Step name\n    Result    string           // Result to trigger on\n    To        string           // Target step (or \"done\"/\"abort\")\n    OutputMap []OutputMapping  // Extract vars from step output\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n    EnvVar string      // Environment variable name\n    Path   OutputPath  // JSON path (e.g., .result[0].id)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. PORTS & INTERFACES\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n#### **AgentAdapter** - Executes a single agent step\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\nImplementations:\n- `prompt.Adapter` - Claude Code / agent commands\n- `generic.Adapter` - Shell script execution\n\n#### **ContainerRuntime** - Docker/local execution\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx, containerID, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\n// Optional interface\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n#### **RunStore** - Persistence\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx, run *domain.Run) error\n    ListRuns(ctx) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsFiltered(ctx, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. ADAPTERS\n\n#### **Docker Runtime** (`internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`)\n**Start Process**:\n1. Build `docker create` command with args:\n   - `--workdir /workspace`\n   - `--user root` (for default cmd wrapper)\n   - `-e CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run_id>`\n   - Copy ANTHROPIC_API_KEY if set\n   - Support `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` and `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n\n2. Copy project to container via `docker cp` (no bind mount)\n3. Copy `.cloche/overrides/` on top (optional)\n4. Copy Claude auth files (`~/.claude/`, `~/.claude.json`)\n5. Start container with `docker start`\n\n**Default Command Wrapper** (when using standard agent):\n- Root user runs chown + cleanup script\n- Strips `.serena` directory (performance)\n- Disables plugins in `.claude/settings.json`\n- Execs as `agent` user with actual command\n\n#### **Prompt Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`)\n**Configuration**:\n- `Commands`: Ordered fallback chain (e.g., `[\"claude\"]`)\n- `ExplicitArgs`: Override default args (e.g., `[\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\"]`)\n- `StatusWriter`: Optional real-time output streaming\n\n**Execution Flow**:\n1. Check `max_attempts` config; return `\"give-up\"` if exceeded\n2. Increment attempt counter\n3. Assemble full prompt (see `assemblePrompt()`)\n4. Try each command in fallback chain:\n   - Parse stdin as prompt\n   - Capture stdout (or stream via StatusWriter)\n   - Extract Claude Code stream-json events:\n     - `\"assistant\"` events → extract text + tool summaries\n     - `\"result\"` events → final result with CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n5. Classify result:\n   - Exit 0 + output = `\"success\"` (or marker result)\n   - Exit 0 + no output = `\"fail\"` (auth/config error)\n   - Exit non-zero + marker = marker result\n   - Exit non-zero + no marker = `\"fail\"` + error message\n6. On success, reset attempt counter; write output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n**Stream JSON Parsing** (`extractStreamText()`):\n- Decodes JSON event, identifies type\n- `\"assistant\"`: Extracts text blocks + tool_use summaries (e.g., \"--- Tool: Read('file.txt') ---\")\n- `\"result\"`: Contains final text with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker\n\n#### **Generic Adapter** (`internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go`)\n**Execution**:\n1. Run shell command via `sh -c`\n2. Pass env vars: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`\n3. Capture stdout (optional: stream via StatusWriter)\n4. Extract result marker from output\n5. Write cleaned output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n\n---\n\n### 6. EXECUTION ENGINE\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n**Workflow Execution Model**:\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor      // Delegates step execution\n    status         StatusHandler     // Status callbacks\n    maxSteps       int               // Limit (default 1000)\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration     // Per-step timeout\n}\n\n// Main loop algorithm:\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**Algorithm**:\n1. Validate workflow + config\n2. Create Run, mark as running\n3. Launch entry step in goroutine\n4. Event loop processes results channel:\n   - **On step complete**:\n     - Record result\n     - Lookup wires for `(step, result)` pair\n     - Launch target steps (fanout support)\n     - Fire matching `collect` conditions\n   - **On wire missing**: Check if any collect handles it; error if neither\n   - **On execution error**: Fail workflow\n5. Track `doneCount` and `aborted` flag\n6. Determine final state:\n   - `aborted` OR error → `RunStateFailed`\n   - `doneCount > 0` → `RunStateSucceeded`\n   - Else → `RunStateFailed`\n\n**Concurrency**:\n- Each step runs in separate goroutine\n- Results channel for completion signaling\n- Main loop is single-threaded (protects Run state)\n\n**Timeouts**:\n- Per-step timeout from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Fallback to engine default (30 min)\n- Context cancellation kills step goroutine\n\n---\n\n### 7. DAEMON gRPC SERVER\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n#### **ClocheServer Structure**:\n```go\ntype ClocheServer struct {\n    store        ports.RunStore\n    captures     ports.CaptureStore\n    logStore     ports.LogStore\n    container    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    defaultImage string\n    evolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    logBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    runIDs       map[string]string      // run_id → container_id\n    loops        map[string]*host.Loop  // project_dir → orchestration loop\n}\n```\n\n#### **RunWorkflow() RPC Flow**:\n1. Check if workflow is host or container (`host.FindHostWorkflows()`)\n2. **If host**: Call `runHostWorkflow()` → dispatch to `host.Runner` → return immediately\n3. **If container**:\n   - Generate unique run ID\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run_id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Create Run record in store (state: pending)\n   - Launch `launchAndTrack()` in background\n   - Return run_id immediately\n\n#### **launchAndTrack() Background Process**:\n1. Ensure image exists (rebuild if Dockerfile changed)\n2. Capture git HEAD SHA (for result branch creation)\n3. Start container via `container.Start()`\n4. Update Run: state=running, containerID=X\n5. Call `trackRun()` to monitor agent output\n\n#### **trackRun() - Status Parsing**:\n1. Attach to agent stdout via `container.AttachOutput()`\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages:\n   ```go\n   type StatusMessage struct {\n       Type      MessageType  // step_started|step_completed|run_completed|run_title|log|error\n       StepName  string\n       Result    string\n       Message   string\n       Timestamp time.Time\n   }\n   ```\n3. Handle each message:\n   - `step_started`: Record in Run.ActiveSteps\n   - `step_completed`: Update Run.StepExecutions\n   - `run_title`: Set Run.Title if empty\n   - `run_completed`: Capture reported result\n   - `error`: Capture error message\n   - `log`: Publish via logBroadcast (for cloche logs)\n\n4. Extract output files from container to `.cloche/<run_id>/output/`\n5. Extract results to git branch (`cloche/<run_id>` branch) via `docker.ExtractResults()`\n6. Finalize Run state:\n   - If `reportedResult == \"succeeded\"` → `RunStateSucceeded`\n   - Else → `RunStateFailed`\n7. Fire evolution trigger if configured\n8. Container cleanup:\n   - Failed runs: always keep\n   - Successful + `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful, no `--keep-container`: remove\n\n---\n\n### 8. HOST WORKFLOW EXECUTION\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` + `executor.go`\n\n#### **Runner - Orchestration**:\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher       // Dispatches container workflows\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    Captures      ports.CaptureStore\n    LogBroadcast  *logstream.Broadcaster\n    TaskID        string              // From daemon loop\n    ExtraEnv      []string            // Additional env vars\n    SkipRunRecord bool                // For list-tasks polling\n}\n```\n\n**Execution** (`runNamedWorkflow()`):\n1. Find workflow in `.cloche/*.cloche` files\n2. Create output directory `.cloche/<run_id>/output`\n3. Create host Run record (if not skipping)\n4. Create Executor + Engine\n5. Run workflow via engine\n6. Persist final state\n7. Return RunResult\n\n#### **Executor - Step Implementation**:\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string              // Host project root\n    MainDir       string              // Worktree dir for scripts\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string              // `.cloche/<run_id>/output/`\n    Wires         []domain.Wire       // For output mappings\n    HostRunID     string              // Parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string            // Workflow-level agent config\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n```\n\n**Step Types**:\n\n1. **Script** (`executeScript()`):\n   - Run shell command via `sh -c`\n   - Working dir: MainDir (worktree) or ProjectDir\n   - Env vars:\n     - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=<project>`\n     - `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT=<run_id>/<step>.out`\n     - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<run_id>`\n     - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID=<task_id>` (if set)\n     - `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT=<previous_step_output>` (if available)\n     - Resolved output mappings from wires\n   - Extract result marker from output\n   - Write output to `.cloche/<run_id>/output/<step>.out`\n\n2. **Workflow** (`executeWorkflow()`):\n   - Dispatch container workflow via gRPC RPC\n   - Read prompt from previous step output (or `prompt_step` override)\n   - Link child run to parent (set `ParentRunID`)\n   - Poll run state every 2 seconds until terminal\n   - Map run state to result: `succeeded` → `success`, else → `fail`\n   - Write run ID to step output (for downstream steps)\n\n3. **Agent** (`executeAgent()`):\n   - Use prompt adapter (Claude Code)\n   - Workflow/step-level agent config (commands, args)\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run_id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Execute adapter\n   - Copy output to executor's output dir\n\n**Output Mappings** (`resolveOutputMappings()`):\n- For each wire to step with output mappings:\n  - Read source step's output\n  - Evaluate path (JSON navigation)\n  - Return `KEY=value` strings\n  - Add to step's environment\n\n---\n\n### 9. HOST ORCHESTRATION LOOP\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n**Orchestration Loop** (`Loop` struct):\n- Monitors project for task changes (via `list-tasks` workflow)\n- Auto-runs main/evolve workflows based on:\n  - `config.Concurrency` (max parallel runs)\n  - `config.StaggerSeconds` (delay between launches)\n  - `config.DedupSeconds` (coalesce rapid task updates)\n  - `config.StopOnError` (halt on unrecovered error)\n  - Evolution-discovered improvements\n\n**Workflow Types**:\n1. `list-tasks`: Discovers available tasks\n2. `main`: Primary task execution (container workflow dispatch)\n3. `evolve`: Self-improvement (powered by evolution trigger)\n4. `finalize`: Post-run cleanup/merge (if defined)\n\n---\n\n### 10. CLI AGENT (PROMPT ADAPTER)\n\n**Key Feature - Conversation Resume via `-c` flag**:\n\nThe prompt adapter in host.cloche can resume Claude Code conversations:\n\n```go\n// From prompt.go:\ndefaultAgentArgs = map[string][]string{\n    \"claude\": {\"-p\", \"--output-format\", \"stream-json\", \"--verbose\", \"--dangerously-skip-permissions\"},\n}\n\n// Conversation IDs passed via env or config:\n// CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND=\"claude -c <conversation_id>\"\n```\n\n**Stream JSON Processing**:\n- Claude Code emits `--output-format stream-json`\n- Each line is a JSON event:\n  - `\"assistant\"` type: New message with content blocks\n  - `\"result\"` type: Final result with CLOCHE_RESULT marker\n- Adapter extracts text and tool summaries in real-time\n- Publishes to logBroadcaster for `cloche logs` streaming\n\n---\n\n### 11. WORKFLOW DSL\n\n**File**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Syntax Example**:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n    container {\n        image: \"cloche-agent:latest\"\n        agent_command: \"claude\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"analyze\" {\n        agent\n        prompt: \"prompts/analyze.txt\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n        max_attempts: \"3\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"test\" {\n        script\n        run: \"make test\"\n        results: [\"pass\", \"fail\"]\n        timeout: \"10m\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"merge\" {\n        script\n        run: \"git merge main\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"conflict\"]\n    }\n    \n    analyze: success → test\n    test: pass → merge\n    test: fail → done\n    merge: success → done\n    merge: conflict → abort\n}\n```\n\n**Host Workflow Example**:\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n    host {\n        agent_command: \"claude\"\n    }\n    \n    step \"generate\" {\n        agent\n        prompt: \"prompts/task.txt\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    step \"run_workflow\" {\n        workflow_name: \"develop\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    step \"merge\" {\n        script\n        run: \"bash scripts/merge.sh\"\n        results: [\"success\", \"fail\"]\n    }\n    \n    generate: success → run_workflow\n    run_workflow: success → merge\n    merge: success → done\n    merge: fail → abort\n}\n```\n\n**Key Parsing Features**:\n- `ParseAll()`: Multiple workflows, auto-detects host vs container\n- `host {}` or `container {}` blocks determine location\n- Workflow-level + step-level config inheritance\n- Output mapping syntax: `output.map: { STEP_VAR: \".path.to.field\" }`\n- Collects: Fan-in multiple branches with `collect all|any`\n\n---\n\n### 12. KEY FILES REFERENCE\n\n| Component | File(s) |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **CLI** | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` |\n| **Daemon** | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` |\n| **Agent** | `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` |\n| **Domain** | `/workspace/internal/domain/{run,workflow}.go` |\n| **Ports** | `/workspace/internal/ports/{agent,container,store}.go` |\n| **gRPC** | `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` + `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` |\n| **Docker** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` |\n| **Prompt Adapter** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` |\n| **Generic Adapter** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` |\n| **Engine** | `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` |\n| **Host Runner** | `/workspace/internal/host/{runner,executor}.go` |\n| **DSL Parser** | `/workspace/internal/dsl/{parser,lexer}.go` |\n| **SQLite Store** | `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` |\n| **Status Protocol** | `/workspace/internal/protocol/{status,result}.go` |\n\n---\n\n### 13. EXECUTION FLOW SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─ CLI: cloche run --workflow develop\n│\n├─→ gRPC: RunWorkflow()\n│\n├─→ [Container Workflow]\n│   ├─ Create Run (pending)\n│   ├─ Start Docker container (async)\n│   ├─ Agent runs: engine.Run(workflow)\n│   │  ├─ Launch entry step (goroutine)\n│   │  ├─ Await result via channel\n│   │  ├─ Wire to next steps\n│   │  └─ Repeat until done/abort\n│   ├─ Parse agent status JSON → update Run\n│   ├─ Extract output files from container\n│   ├─ Extract results to git branch\n│   └─ Finalize Run state\n│\n└─ [Host Workflow]\n    ├─ Create Run (host=true)\n    ├─ host.Runner.Run(project, \"main\")\n    ├─ Parse host.cloche\n    ├─ Execute steps via Executor:\n    │  ├─ Script: sh -c <cmd>\n    │  ├─ Workflow: dispatch container via gRPC (wait)\n    │  └─ Agent: prompt adapter on host\n    ├─ Record step outputs in .cloche/<run_id>/output/\n    └─ Finalize host Run state\n```\n\n---\n\nThis architecture enables **self-evolving containerized development workflows** with strong separation of concerns: domain logic, storage, container runtimes, and agent adapters are all pluggable via ports."}],"totalDurationMs":123509,"totalTokens":81949,"totalToolUseCount":45,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1167,"cache_read_input_tokens":74059,"output_tokens":6723,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1167},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
